Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时在夜深人静的时候\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Sometimes Dr. Lecter and I would talk{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.20,0:00:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生会和我聊聊天\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}when things got quiet enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.29,0:00:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谈我所选修的科学课程\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}about the science courses I was takin'.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那种邮购的心理学课程 也能称为科学?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Some kind of mail-order courses in psychology, Nurse Barney?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.42,0:00:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不是\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No, sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.92,0:00:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不认为心理学是科学\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I don't consider psychology a science{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔医生也不这么想\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and neither did Dr. Lecter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.18,0:01:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么 巴尼...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Now, Barney...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你在收容所工作的时候\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}while you were working at the asylum{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.43,0:01:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的确看到史黛琳和汉尼拔之间有互动关系\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}you observed Clarice Starling and Hannibal Lecter interacting.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.57,0:01:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,互动?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Interacting?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.36,0:01:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是聊天之类的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Talking to one another.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.19,0:01:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 他们看起来好像是...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes. Yes, it seemed to me that they...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.07,0:01:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你很想拿这笔咨询费\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I can see you're eager to justify your consulting fee{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.70,0:01:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是只说你看到的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but why don't we start with what you saw{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.95,0:01:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别把自己的想法加进去\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}not what you thought about what you saw?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.08,0:01:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德 别这样 他当然可以表达自己的意见\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cordell, don't be like that. Barney can give us his opinion.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.63,0:01:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼 告诉我们你的看法\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Barney, give us your opinion of what you saw.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.92,0:01:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得他们之间是哪种关系?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What was it between them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.67,0:01:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通常汉尼拔医生根本不理会来访的观察员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Most of the time, Dr. Lecter didn't respond at all to visitors.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至会不发一言的瞪着前来观察的学生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He'd just, for instance, open his eyes long enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.85,0:01:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让他们觉得难堪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to insult some academic who was there to look over him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.57,0:01:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他却回答史黛琳的问话\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}With Starling, he answered her questions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.27,0:01:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她引起了他的兴趣 也被她深深的吸引住\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She interested him. She intrigued him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:02:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认为她既迷人又有趣\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He thought she was charming and amusing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以史黛琳和汉尼拔...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}So Clarice Starling and Hannibal Lecter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就变成了朋友\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}became friendly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.62,0:02:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错 是一种形而上的朋友\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Inside a kind of formal structure, yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.63,0:02:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么说来他很喜欢她?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And he was fond of her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.50,0:02:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼 谢谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Thank you, Barney.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你的坦白\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Thank you very much for your candor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.97,0:02:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于你卖给我的那些...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And keep all those wonderful items...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.35,0:02:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔的珍贵收藏品\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}from your personal Lecter treasure trove coming.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.14,0:02:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常喜欢\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I've enjoyed them immensely.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.01,0:02:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Mr. Verger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.81,0:02:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喔 我差点忘了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Oh, I almost forgot.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德 我能吃块甜点吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I might be able to get a cookie down. What do you say, Cordell?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.19,0:02:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会要了你的命\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I think it would kill you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.28,0:02:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-多少钱?  -二十五...万\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-How much? -Two hundred and fifty...thousand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:03:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去开张二十五万的支票\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cut a check for $250,000.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.25,0:03:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,片名:  人魔
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.11,0:04:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种时候她也能睡?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How can she sleep at a time like this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:05:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她昨晚出勤 现在正养精蓄锐\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She's on a jump-out squad all night. She's saving her strength.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说从华府警局 来了个叫柏顿的家伙\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We got some guy named Bolton from the DC Police.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.53,0:05:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家请注意 这是现场区域图\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}All right, everyone. Pay attention. Here's the layout.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.57,0:05:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我是华府警探柏顿\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Excuse me. I'm Officer Bolton, DC Police.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 从警徽上我可以看出来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I can see that from your badge. How do you do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是这里的负责人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'm in charge here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.36,0:05:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿警探 我是史黛琳探员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Officer Bolton, I'm Special Agent Starling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.66,0:05:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了避免不必要的误会\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Just so we don't get off on the wrong foot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我解释一下我们来此的目的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}let me explain why we're all here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对艾微达很了解 因为我曾逮捕过她两次\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'm here because I know Evelda Drumgo. I arrested her twice on RICO warrants.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:05:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次因为牵涉到毒品和枪械\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}DEA and ATF, in addition to backing me up{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,禁药取缔局和武器管理局 也一起参加行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}are here for the drugs and the weapons.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于你来这里是因为 市长在被判了使用可卡因罪后\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You're here because our mayor wants to appear tough on drugs{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了表现出取缔毒品的决心\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}especially after his own cocaine conviction{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.50,0:06:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才让你们加入我们的行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and hopes he can accomplish that by having you join us here today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小姐 你倒挺凶的嘛\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You got a smart mouth, lady.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不介意 我们可以继续讨论吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If you wouldn't mind, I'd appreciate it if you'd let me continue.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.26,0:06:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 大家看一下\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}All right, take a look.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.36,0:06:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲜鱼市场的后面是水\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Fish market. Back's on the water.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对面是毒品制造所\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Across the street, ground floor, is the meth lab.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"通缉犯"艾微达是爱滋病患者\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Evelda Drumgo's HIV positive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.27,0:06:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,紧要关头她会又抓又咬 你们要小心\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She will spit and bite if cornered, so you should watch it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万一是你在媒体前送她进警车\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If you happen to be the one who puts her in a patrol car in front of the news cameras{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.86,0:06:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿 千万别碰她的头\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Bolton,you don't wanna push her head down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.70,0:06:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她喜欢把针藏在头发里\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She'll likely have a needle in her hair.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好能在室内将她拿下"公共市场"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We want to take her inside the building, not out in the street.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.00,0:06:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家尽量靠近我们的伪装车\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We can get closest with the van.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时候我们从前面进攻 禁药组攻打后面\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If it looks good, on my signal we hit the front, DEA hits the back{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请华府警探去支援禁药组\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}DCPD backin'them up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的瞭望员会守在三条街前\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She'll have her watchers out at least three blocks around.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以便及时给她消息 所以我们不要太招摇\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They've tipped her before in time, so let's not make spectacles of ourselves.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.02,0:07:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-今天挺忙碌的  -没错\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Pretty busy today. -I agree.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.28,0:07:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请给我杯咖啡\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Can I please get a cup of coffee?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.93,0:07:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你看到了吗?  -那表示可以行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Did you see that? -That's a roger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 近来如何?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What's up, man?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.36,0:07:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死 她出来了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Goddamn it. It's her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.82,0:08:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有三个人 都带着枪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}With three guys. They're all packin'.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她胸前挂着东西 是婴儿\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She's carryin' something. She's got a baby.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏汉 人太多\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hey, Brigham, it's too crowded.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看取消比较好\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There are too many people. I say we call it off.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说呢?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What do you say?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.21,0:08:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我同意\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I agree.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.33,0:08:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有单位 行动取消\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}All units, stand down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-威士基知道了  -柏克知道了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Whiskey team copies. -Burke copy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.05,0:08:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是柏顿 我要继续行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is Bolton. Stay on target.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.01,0:08:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柏顿 我已说过取消行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I said all units stand down, Bolton, right now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.80,0:08:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-太晚了 我们已经开始  -柏顿 请你合作\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-It's too late. We're movin'in. -Bolton, he said it's off.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.01,0:08:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不准行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Stand down now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她胸前有婴儿 重复她有婴儿\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She's carrying a baby. I repeat, she's carrying a baby.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有单位不要行动\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}All units stand down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.48,0:08:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-柏顿 把枪收起来  -要命 有人拿枪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Keep that gun down, Bolton. -Damn, dude got a piece.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.60,0:08:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-先杀了他  -快走!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Light his ass up. -It's a go!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.44,0:08:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查局 快趴在地上\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}FBI! Down on the ground!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停火!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hold it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要开枪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hold your fire!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.03,0:09:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别开枪!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Don't!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾微达 你出来!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Evelda, get out of the car!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.66,0:09:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是史黛琳吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Starling, is that you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.50,0:09:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你离开车子!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Step away from the car!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.21,0:09:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把手举起来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Show me your hands, Evelda.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.05,0:09:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请把手举起来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Please. Show me your hands.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你近来好吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How've you been?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.88,0:09:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别这样做\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Don't do this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.68,0:09:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 不会有事的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's all right. It's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.38,0:10:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 宝贝 你吓坏了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I know, I know. Baby, I know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.42,0:10:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别哭\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.96,0:10:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你别哭\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.35,0:10:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.12,0:11:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今早朋友 家人和同事 聚集在阿灵顿国家公墓中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Friends, family and coworkers gathered here this morning at Arlington National Cemetery{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参加因公殉职的武器管制局柏汉探员的丧礼\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to bury BATF Agent John Brigham shot and killed in the line of duty Friday.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他享年四十岁\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He was 40 years old.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场毒品突击 夺去他及另外五个人的生命\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This ill-fated drug raid that claimed his life and five others{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一连串的意外事件 始于德州的瓦库\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is the latest in a seemingly endless series of incidents{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.09,0:11:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于探员们只知使用武力 而不愿运用大脑一事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}in which theJustice Department and the FBI have been questioned{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法部及调查局已受到质询\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}about their use of firepower rather than judgment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.47,0:11:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次的灾难是由调查局探员 史黛琳所引起\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This time it was FBI Special Agent Clarice Starling heading up the calamitous strike force.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.05,0:11:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十年前 为了营救 前田纳西议员的女儿凯瑟琳\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Agent Starling attained some measure of celebrity ten years ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳曾经由"食人魔"汉尼拔医生的协助 得以破案\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}when she was given information by Dr. Hannibal "The Cannibal"Lecter which led to the rescue of Catherine Martin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她因此而声名大噪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}daughter of the former US senator from Tennessee.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.86,0:11:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这个礼拜当她回复工作时 迎接她的不是表扬而是诉讼\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}When she returns to work this week, she won't be so celebrated.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.74,0:11:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为代表被害家属的泰福律师 将控告她误杀至死之罪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Attorney Telford Higgins, representing one of the families of those slain says he will file a wrongful-death suit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.95,0:11:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cordell!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.67,0:12:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德!\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cordell!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有什么吩咐  -替我接司法部\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Yes, sir. -Get me theJustice Department.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.27,0:12:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳探员?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Agent Starling?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是禁药取缔局的约翰 助理执政官诺门\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is John Eldridge from DEA. Assistant Director Noonan, you know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们部门的拉金 他专精责任问题\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Larkin Wayne from our Office of Professional Responsibility.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.20,0:12:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,武器管制局的包勃\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Bob Sneed, ATF.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.28,0:12:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,市长助理班尼 还有司法部的保罗\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Benny Holcombe, assistant to the mayor. And Paul Krendler.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.53,0:12:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该认识他\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You know Paul. Paul's come over from Justice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.16,0:12:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他以非官方身份来协助我们\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}unofficially, as a favor to us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.75,0:12:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说 他并不在这里\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}In other words, he's here, and he's not here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.25,0:12:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你已经看过 报纸和电视的报导吧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}So I take it you've seen the coverage in the papers and on television?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.37,0:12:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些新闻和我无关\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I have nothing to do with the news, Mr. Krendler.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个女人手中抱着婴儿\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The woman had a baby in her arms.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.93,0:12:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,照片就在这里 你应该知道问题有多严重\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There are pictures. You could see the problem, I would think.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:12:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婴儿是在她胸前挂的婴儿袋里\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Not in her arms. In a carrier across her chest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.38,0:12:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她手里拿的是冲锋枪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}In her arms she had a MAC-10.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.64,0:12:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是来帮你的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Look, we're here to help you, Starling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.81,0:13:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这样怒气冲冲的态度 只会使事情更难办\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's gonna be a hell of a lot harder to do with a combative attitude.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能自由发言吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Can I speak freely, Mr. Pearsall?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.15,0:13:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是应你们的要求 来协助做这次突击的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Your agency called this office to get me assigned to help you on this raid.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的确尽力去做\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I tried to do that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.37,0:13:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有人却不遵守我所做的判断\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I clearly expressed my judgment and was ignored.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.46,0:13:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以致牺牲了一位好朋友探员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And now a good agent and a friend is dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了你还杀了五个人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You shot and killed five people out there, Agent Starling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.34,0:13:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道能说这是好的判断吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is that how you define good judgment?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.47,0:13:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一场丑恶的突击\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This raid was an ugly mess.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.67,0:13:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被迫在被杀\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I ended up in a position where I had a choice of dying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.89,0:13:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或射杀身挂婴儿的女人中做选择\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}or shooting a woman carrying a child.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.98,0:13:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我做了选择\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I chose.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.31,0:13:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是射杀她\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I shot her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我杀了带着婴儿的母亲\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I killed a mother holding her child.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很后悔 也恨我自己\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And I regret it. I resent myself for it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.07,0:13:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起 现在要终止这个会议\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Gentlemen, I'm going to call a halt to this meeting{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.65,0:13:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会个别打电话给你们\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and get back to you individually by phone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.45,0:14:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真会浪费时间\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That was a waste of time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳 你居然有秘密仰慕者\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You have a secret admirer, Starling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.62,0:14:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他本身不怎么样 却有身居高位的朋友\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He isn't much to look at, but he does have friends in high places.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.30,0:14:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你记得马森维杰吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Remember Mason Verger?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.21,0:14:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉尼拔的第四个被害人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Lecter's fourth victim.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.88,0:14:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很富有\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The rich one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是唯一死里逃生的人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The only one that survived.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说有些汉尼拔的新资料 但是只愿意告诉你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He says he has some new information on Lecter he'll only share with you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.77,0:14:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么意思? 如有需要 就扣押文件呀\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What do you mean, only share it with me? You want it, seize it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.47,0:14:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-最好别这么做  -我并没有和你讲话\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-I'd rather not. -I wasn't speaking to you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.73,0:14:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我和你讲话时 自然会看着你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}When I speak to you, you'll know it because I'll look at you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不这么做?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Why would we rather not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.57,0:14:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上次他因为我们把汉尼拔从 十大通缉犯中除去而打电话来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The last time he called was when we took Lecter off the Ten Most Wanted List.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很生气 我们对他说"嘿 你最好接受"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He was upset about that. We said, "Hey, that's life."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.87,0:14:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说:参议院的失察委员会"爱序山庄"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He said, "This is a Senate Oversight Committee{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会给你们好看的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to make your life miserable."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.95,0:14:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他家族对政治上献金一向慷慨\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}His family's political contributions may not be enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.05,0:14:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然买不起参议员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to buy a senator{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是绝对租得起\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but they are enough to rent them from time to time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.67,0:15:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,况且他若真有线索 我们又何必惹他生气\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There's no reason to go through that if he really does have something new.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.35,0:15:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳 其实这件事对你有利\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's a good deal for you, Starling. You can't pretend it isn't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你能再回去侦办知名案件\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Get to go back on a celebrated case.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.81,0:15:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,媒体方面 我会替你去和他们交涉\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'll take care of the media for your Drumgo killing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.27,0:15:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都高兴\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Everyone's gonna be happy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不高兴\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'm not happy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.90,0:15:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许你根本就不会高兴\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Well, maybe you're incapable of being happy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.73,0:15:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗先生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Mr. Krendler{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.20,0:15:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道做为一个探员 随时都有死亡的危险\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}out on the street, you know you might take a bullet in the line of duty.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果怕死 那就不要做\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You accept it or you get out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们接受这个事实\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You live with it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.95,0:15:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但所不能接受的是\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What you don't expect or accept{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.75,0:15:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你按照所受过的训练 和上级的指示去做\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}is taking one in the back in your boss's office{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而结果却背上黑锅\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}for doing your job exactly as they've taught you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.75,0:15:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这才叫人气愤\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That makes you unhappy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.50,0:15:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳 你说得不错\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Of course you're right, Starling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但毕竟改变不了什么\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but it doesn't change anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.05,0:15:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它改变了一切 连我在内\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It changes everything. It changes me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 我叫柯德 是维杰先生的私人医生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hi, I'm Cordell Doemling, Mr. Verger's private physician.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.19,0:16:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How do you do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.85,0:16:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,麻烦你把车停到那边\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If you'd be so kind as to park down at the end.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.61,0:16:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你的眼睛能适应这个昏暗光线\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}One's eyes adjust to the darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生 史黛琳探员来了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Mr. Verger, Agent Starling is here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.22,0:17:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你早 维杰先生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Good morning, Mr. Verger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.09,0:17:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你开的是福特野马吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Was that a Mustang I heard out there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes, it was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.73,0:17:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5000c.c.的引擎?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Five-liter?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那好快呀\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Fast.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.89,0:17:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德 你可以离开了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cordell, I think you can leave us now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我留下来可能会有用\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I thought I might stay. Perhaps I could be useful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去看我的午餐准备得如何\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You could be useful seeing about my lunch.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不介意我把麦克风 夹在你的衣服或枕头上吧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'll attach this microphone to your clothing or pillow, if that's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.50,0:17:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}By all means.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:17:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样会比较容易些\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Here, this should make it easier.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.39,0:18:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对发生在我身上的事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You know, I thank God{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.98,0:18:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须感谢上帝\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}for what happened.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.89,0:18:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这是赎罪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It was my salvation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.39,0:18:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳探员 你信主吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Have you accepted Jesus, Agent Starling?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你有信仰吗?  -我家人信奉路德教派\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Do you have faith? -I was raised Lutheran.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.40,0:18:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是我问的问题\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That's not what I asked.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.07,0:18:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是5143690号史黛琳探员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is Special Agent Clarice Starling, 5143690{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.54,0:18:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我作证在三月二十日 维杰已经发誓会说实话\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}deposing Mason R. Verger on March 20, sworn and attested.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.45,0:18:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想说我童年时代 在夏令营里的快乐时光\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I want to tell you about summer camp. It was a wonderful childhood experience.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-等会儿再谈吧  -我现在就要说\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-We can get to that later. -We can get to it now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这些全有关联\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You see, it all comes to bear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是在我父亲所创办的基督夏令营里\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It was a Christian camp my father founded{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.17,0:18:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它专门收容孤苦无依的孩子们\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}for poor, unfortunate, cast-off little boys and girls{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了一块糖 他们愿做任何事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}who would do anything for a candy bar.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维杰先生 我对你的恋童癖不感兴趣\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Mr. Verger, I don't need to know about the sex offenses.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没关系 在美国律师之前我已免疫\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's all right. I have immunity from the US Attorney.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.77,0:18:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至在上帝面前\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And I have immunity{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.03,0:19:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也免疫了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}from the risen Jesus.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为没人禁得起巧克力糖的诱惑\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And nobody beats the Riz.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.32,0:19:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在法院指派汉尼拔医生给你前 你是否已经认识他?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Had you ever seen Dr. Lecter before the court assigned you to him for therapy?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.65,0:19:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你指的是?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What do you mean?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,社交上的认识?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Socially?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 你介意谈论它吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It is what I mean, yes, if you don't mind talking about it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.79,0:19:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会 我并不引以为耻\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No, not at all. I'm not ashamed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.87,0:19:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我没这么说  -我们认识得很平常\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-I didn't say you should be. -No, we met conventionally{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.21,0:19:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是医师和病人的关系\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}as doctor and patient.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他怎么会到你住处去?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How did he end up at your house?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.21,0:19:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然是我邀他的罗\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I invited him, of course{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我邀他到我的临时住所去\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to my pied-a-terre.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我穿着最诱人的衣服去开门\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I came to the door in my nicest come-hither outfit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.31,0:19:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我担心...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I was concerned...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.39,0:19:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可能会怕我\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}that he'd be afraid of me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他似乎一点也不在乎\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But he didn't seem to be afraid of me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.32,0:19:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在想起来是很可疑\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That's almost funny now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.77,0:19:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把我的性玩具拿给他看\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I showed him my toys{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.95,0:19:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中包括那套活结装置\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}my noose setup, among other things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.95,0:20:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是可以把自己吊起来 却又不会窒息的装置\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's where you sort of hang yourself, but not really.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.28,0:20:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那种感觉真好 如果...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It feels good while you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.29,0:20:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正你能想像得出来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}well, you know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.42,0:20:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总归...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Anyway...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.79,0:20:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他说"维杰"  -维杰 要不要来点兴奋剂?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-he said, "Mason," -Mason, would you like a popper?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.29,0:20:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说"哇!当然要"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And I said, "Would I? Oh, wow!"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.89,0:20:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,药效出来后 我兴奋到极点\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Once that kicked in, I was flying.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.68,0:20:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说"让我看看你那种"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He said, "Mason, show me how you smile{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.64,0:20:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"能赢得小孩信任的笑容"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to gain the confidence of a child."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.31,0:20:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我笑起来时...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}When I smiled...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.36,0:20:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他又说"我看出来 他们为什么会信任你"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}he said, "Oh, I see how you do it."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,医生手里拿着 镜子的碎片朝我走来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The good doctor approached me with a piece of broken mirror.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.16,0:20:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"试试用这个"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}"Try this."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.45,0:20:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你脸上的肉割下来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Try peeling off your face{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.07,0:20:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后拿去喂狗吃\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And feeding it to the dogs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行 我还是看得到你的笑容\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No, I can still see it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.93,0:20:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来一次\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Try again.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是不行\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No, I'm afraid not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是所谓的娱乐\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That's entertainment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.76,0:21:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说实话 当时似乎觉得很好玩\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Well, it seemed like a good idea at the time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你提到最近又有新的线索\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You indicated to me that you'd received some kind of new information.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.07,0:21:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,柯德\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cordell.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是怎么来的?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Where did this come from?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.21,0:21:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寄来的 两个星期前到的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Buenos Aires. I received it two weeks ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.18,0:21:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面的信封呢?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Where's the package it came in?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.84,0:21:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问得好 上面并没有写什么重要的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Good question. There was nothing written on it of interest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.43,0:21:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是不是扔了?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Did we throw it out?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.44,0:21:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 实在很抱歉\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes, I'm afraid we did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:21:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看这个会有帮助吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Oh, dear. You think it'll help?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.35,0:21:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但愿如此\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I hope so.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:22:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望能帮你捉到他\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I hope it'll help you catch him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.52,0:22:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以雪你这次不名誉的耻辱\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}to help cleanse the stigma of your recent dishonor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.45,0:22:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你 我走了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Thank you. That's all I need.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你在收容所 和汉尼拔医生谈话时\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Did you find some rapport with Dr. Lecter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.24,0:22:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有对他产生信赖感?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}in your talks at the asylum?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我在割自己脸时 曾经有过那种感觉\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I know I did while I was peeling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.04,0:22:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是用文明的方法交换心得\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We exchanged information in a civil way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.04,0:22:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但还是隔着一层玻璃\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But always through the glass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.62,0:22:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.43,0:22:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你很奇怪?  -为什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Isn't it funny? -What's that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.52,0:22:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对我的脸无动于衷\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You can look at my face{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.85,0:22:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是一听我提上帝 反儿使你胆怯\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but you shied when I said the name of God.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-找到你要找的吗?  -你确定只有这些?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Finding what you want? -Are you sure this is all of it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.88,0:23:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到目前为止 只剩这些\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}That's all there is now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.97,0:23:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本来不止的 可惜被人一点一点的拿走了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There was more, but it's been picked over little by little over the years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.93,0:23:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些东西在特定市场中 能值不少钱\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You know, this stuff s worth a lot of money in certain circles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.19,0:23:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像这里的可卡因一样\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's kind of like the cocaine that disappears around here{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.57,0:23:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点一点的消失掉\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}little by little.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.54,0:23:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,*巴尔的摩州立法医医院*
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 巴尼\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hey, Barney.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.40,0:24:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还记得我吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Remember me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.86,0:25:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳探员 请你声明 你并没有把权益念给我听\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Would you agree for the record, Agent Starling that I've not been read my rights?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.28,0:25:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我声明巴尼并不知道他的权益\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I have not Mirandized Barney. He is unaware of his rights.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.79,0:25:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你把汉尼拔医生 交给田纳西警局后\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}So when you turned Dr. Lecter over to the Tennessee police{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.25,0:25:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们对他无礼 如今都死了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They weren't civil to him. They're all dead now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.42,0:25:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实际上他们只活了三天\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They only survived his company three days.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.83,0:25:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你却活了六年\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You survived him six years at the asylum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.76,0:25:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么做到的? 我觉得这和礼貌无关\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How'd you do that? It wasn't just being civil.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.01,0:25:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有很大的关系\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes, it was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.84,0:25:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他逃走后 你有没有想过他可能来找你?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Did you ever think, after he escaped, he might come after you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.19,0:25:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.31,0:25:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他曾对我说过在可能的情况下\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He once told me that, whenever feasible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.69,0:25:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他宁愿吃无礼之人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}he preferred to eat the rude.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.85,0:25:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫他们"无礼鼠类" 你呢?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}"Free-range rude," he called 'em. What about you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.06,0:25:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有想过他 或想过他可能会来找你?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You ever think he might come after you? You ever think about him at all?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.49,0:25:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天都会想上三十秒\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}At least 30 seconds of every day. I can't help it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.95,0:25:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像坏习惯一样 戒也戒不掉\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He's always with me, like a bad habit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.16,0:26:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的东西 像书 纸 和图画等等都到哪里去了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do you know what happened to his stuff  his books, papers, drawings?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.17,0:26:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收容所关闭时 所有的东西都丢了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Everything got thrown away when the place closed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.96,0:26:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,节省经费嘛\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Cutbacks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.25,0:26:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现由汉尼拔医生 签名的那本烹饪之乐杂志\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I just found out that Dr. Lecter's signed copy of TheJoy of Cooking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.55,0:26:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近被私人收藏家 以一万六千美金买进\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}sold to a private collector for $16,000.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.22,0:26:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕是仿造品\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It was probably a fake.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.47,0:26:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卖主切结书上的签名是 "费凯伦"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The seller's affidavit of ownership was signed "Karen Phlox."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.56,0:26:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该认识她\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do you know Karen Phlox? You should.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.89,0:26:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她曾替你填过工作申请表 最后签上"巴尼"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}She filled out your employment application, but signed it "Barney."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.77,0:26:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有退税单也一样\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Same thing on your tax returns.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.95,0:26:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你要书 我会试着把它要回来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You want the book? Maybe I can get it back.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.95,0:26:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当他攻击护士时 你曾打断 他的手臂 我要那张X光片\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I want the x-ray of Lecter's arm you broke in the attack on that nurse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.46,0:26:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有其它被你拿走的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and everything else you've got.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.54,0:26:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在夜深人静 尖叫声平息之后\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We used to talk about a lot of things at night{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.34,0:26:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们时常聊天\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}after the screamin' finally died down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.88,0:27:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时也谈到你 你想知道他都说些什么吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}We talked about you sometimes. You wanna know what he said?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.43,0:27:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把X光片给我\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Go get the x-ray.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.77,0:27:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是个坏人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'm not a bad guy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.86,0:27:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没说你是坏人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I didn't say you were.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.53,0:27:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奇顿医生才是坏人\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Dr. Chilton was a bad guy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.11,0:27:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你第一次访问汉尼拔医生后 他就开始录你们的谈话\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}After your first visit, he started taping your conversations with Lecter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.75,0:27:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们非常有价值\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}These are valuable.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.75,0:27:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你走吧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Go on now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.88,0:27:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已经哀吊得够久了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You've grieved long enough.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.51,0:27:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是怎么说的?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And what'd he say?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.71,0:27:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在晚上他怎么说我的?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What'd he say about me late at night?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.06,0:27:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他谈到遗传和内心深处的行为\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He was talking about inherited, hardwired behavior.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用鹞鸽的遗传来做比方\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}He was using genetics in the roller pigeons as an example.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.06,0:27:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们喜欢高高的飞到天上 然后炫耀的翻着筋斗俯冲下来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They fly up in the air, roll backwards in a display, fallin' to the ground.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.86,0:28:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鹞鸽分为肤浅和深沉两种\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}There are shallow rollers, and there are deep rollers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是当两只深沉鹞鸽结合后\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You can't breed two deep rollers{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的后代往往会\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}or their young, their offspring, will roll all the way down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.74,0:28:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俯冲撞地而死\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}hit and die.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.12,0:28:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,巴尼 史黛琳探员是只深沉的鹞鸽\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Agent Starling is a deep roller, Barney.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.24,0:28:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只希望她父母中有一个是只肤浅的鹞鸽\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Let us hope one of her parents was not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.91,0:28:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你并没有离开正轨\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Surely the odd confluence of events hasn't escaped you, Clarice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.96,0:28:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为杰克在我面前向你挑战\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Jack Crawford dangles you in front of me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.92,0:28:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我才给你一些帮助\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}then I give you a bit of help.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.71,0:28:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你以为是因为...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do you think it's because I like to look at you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.10,0:28:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢边看你边想着你会有多可口吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and imagine how good you would taste{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.10,0:28:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是这样吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Clarice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.51,0:28:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 难道是真的?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I don't know. Is it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.27,0:28:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我待在这个房间里已经八年\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I've been in this room for eight years now, Clarice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.61,0:28:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道在我有生之年 他们是不会让我出去的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I know they will never, ever let me out while I'm alive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.98,0:28:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想能看外面的风景\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What I want is a view.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.20,0:28:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我一扇窗户 让我能看到树甚至河流\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I want a window where I can see a tree or even water.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.16,0:28:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想转到联邦收容所去 那样才能远离奇顿医生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I want to be in a federal institution far away from Dr. Chilton.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.64,0:29:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡波尼图书馆中的书信 可以追溯到十三世纪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The Capponi correspondence goes back to the 13th century.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.18,0:29:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于在费尔博士手中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Dr. Fell might hold in his hand{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.05,0:29:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那非意大利人的手中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}his non-Italian hand{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.18,0:29:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很可能握有但丁的真迹\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}a note from Dante Alighieri himself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.69,0:29:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他能分辨出真伪吗? 我不认为\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But would he recognize it? I think not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.73,0:29:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位 你们已经肯定 他对意大利中叶的辨认能力\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Gentlemen, you have examined him in medieval Italian{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.19,0:29:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也承认对一个外国人来说\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and I will not deny that his language is admirable{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.91,0:29:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的文字实在美妙\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}for a straniero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.20,0:29:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他是否真正具有 文艺复兴前佛罗伦斯的气质\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But is he acquainted with the personalities of the pre-Renaissance Firenze?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.20,0:29:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我却有所怀疑\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I think not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.28,0:29:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说不定哪天在卡波尼图书馆中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What if he came upon a note in the Capponi library{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.04,0:29:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会声称找到了 诗人卡瓦澄第的真迹\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}say from Guido di Cavalcanti?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.71,0:29:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道他真能分辨出真伪吗? 我不相信\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Would he recognize that? I think not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.58,0:29:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们还在争论吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They're still arguing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.84,0:29:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏立想让他侄子做这份工作\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Sogliato wants the job for his nephew.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.59,0:30:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是学者们似乎对 他们所指定的人很满意\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But the scholars seem satisfied with the temporary guy they appointed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.23,0:30:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倘若他真那么精通但丁\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If he's such an expert on Dante{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.90,0:30:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何不让他 发表一场对但丁研究的演讲\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}let him lecture on Dante to the Studiolo.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.77,0:30:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好面对但丁的爱好者  -好主意\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Let him face them if he can. -I look forward to it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.78,0:30:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就订在十四号好了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Very well. On the 14th.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.42,0:30:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Dr. Fell?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.18,0:30:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫帕齐 是警察总部的督察\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Chief Inspector Rinaldo Pazzi of the questura.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.09,0:30:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,督察 我能帮什么忙?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Commendatore, how can I be of service?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.63,0:30:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我在调查前任馆长 辛诺的失踪案件\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Sorry. I'm investigating the disappearance of your predecessor, Signor di Bonaventura.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.89,0:30:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不知道是否...  -你这么说 好像我已做了馆长\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-I was wondering if...  -"Predecessor" implies I have the job.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.81,0:30:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是希望如此 可惜他们还没决定\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Unfortunately, I don't. Not yet, though I am hopeful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.61,0:31:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只是支薪给我 让我照顾图书馆而已\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They are letting me look after the library for a stipend.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.20,0:31:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以前的调查员\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}The officers who first checked{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.40,0:31:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有找到遗书或自杀信\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}didn't find any sort of farewell or suicide note.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.58,0:31:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你能...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I was wondering if you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.21,0:31:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我在抽屉或书中 找到任何有用的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If I come across anything in the Capponi library stuffed in a drawer or book{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.91,0:31:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定会立刻通知你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'll call you at once.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.96,0:31:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.84,0:31:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被改派任务了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You've been reassigned.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Pardon?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.05,0:31:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得 你本来在调查莫斯楚的案件\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You were on the II Mostro case, I'm sure I read.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.56,0:31:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没错  -现在却查这个案子\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Yes, that's right. -Now you're on this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.98,0:31:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就我所知 这不是什么大案子\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is much less grand a case, I would think.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.02,0:31:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果以知名度而言...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Well, if I thought of my work in those terms{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.78,0:31:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的不错\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}yes, I guess I'd agree.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.15,0:31:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-调查失踪人口  -你说什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-A missing person. -Sorry?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.65,0:31:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为不平等待遇 还是因为你的能力不够?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Were you unfairly dismissed from the grander case, or did you deserve it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.70,0:31:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费尔博士 让我们再回到原题\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Regarding this one, Dr. Fell{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辛诺的私人物品 是否仍在图书馆内?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}are the signore's personal effects still at the Palazzo?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.09,0:32:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一共装了四大箱 还有清单\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Packed neatly in four cases with an inventory.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.71,0:32:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是没有遗书\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Alas, no note.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.92,0:32:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会叫人来取 谢谢你的帮忙\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I'll send someone over to pick them up. Thank you for your help.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.15,0:32:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 谢谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hey, thanks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.53,0:32:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进行的如何?有线索吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}How's it going? Any leads?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.69,0:32:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是线索 可惜就是找不到他\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yeah, they're all leads. They just don't lead to him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.54,0:32:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真佩服你能天天和这些为伍\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I don't know how you live with this stuff.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.62,0:32:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呀\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Oh, God.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.17,0:32:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这封是世界记录给我的恭贺函\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This is from the Guinness Book of World Records congratulating me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.88,0:32:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说我创下 女调查员中杀人最多的记录\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}on being the female FBI agent who has shot and killed the most people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.07,0:33:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能不能请你离开一下\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Would you excuse me, please?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.08,0:33:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Sure.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.68,0:33:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亲爱的史黛琳\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Dear Clarice{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.65,0:33:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认真追踪你这次的受辱事件\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I've followed with enthusiasm the course of your disgrace and public shaming.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.77,0:33:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对自己的受辱并不在乎\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}My own never bothered me except for the inconvenience{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.15,0:33:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只对失去自由有所不满\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}of being incarcerated.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.06,0:34:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你的眼界 却让我操心\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But you may lack perspective.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.74,0:34:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从我们在地牢中的讨论中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}In our discussions down in the dungeon{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.95,0:34:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发现 你那位做守夜员的父亲\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}it was apparent to me that your father, the dead night watchman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.87,0:34:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你心目中占有很重的份量\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}figures largely in your value system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.96,0:34:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当初你最得意 能将杰姆绳之以法\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I think your success in putting an end toJame Gumb's career as a couturier{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.33,0:34:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你觉得 那会使你父亲引以为傲\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}pleased you most because you could imagine your father being pleased.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.05,0:34:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜如今你却成了 调查局中的老鼠屎\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But now, alas, you're in bad odor with the FBI.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.93,0:34:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"调查局探员枪杀五人" 你父亲会不会因此\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do you imagine your daddy being shamed by your disgrace?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.72,0:34:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而感到丢脸\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Do you see him in his plain pine box{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.26,0:34:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是否会躺在棺材中 眼见你手刃这份前途无量的工作\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}crushed by your failure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.85,0:34:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而痛心疾首吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}the sorry, petty end of a promising career?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.27,0:34:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这份耻辱最大的影响是什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What is worst about this humiliation, Clarice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.90,0:34:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为你的失败 会影响到你父母的形象?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is it how your failure will reflect on your mommy and daddy?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.11,0:34:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是你害怕从此以后...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is your worst fear that people will now and forever believe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.95,0:34:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们认为他们只是 住在活动房屋中...\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}they were indeed just good old trailer-camp{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.07,0:34:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没用的穷白鬼\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}tornado-bait white trash{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.37,0:34:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而你也和他们一样?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and that perhaps you are too?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.87,0:35:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便一提 我发现在调查局的网页上\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}By the way, I couldn't help noticing on the FBI's rather dull web site{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.08,0:35:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我居然从普通罪犯\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}that I've been hoisted from the Bureau's archives of the common criminal{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.05,0:35:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,升级到十大通缉犯\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and elevated to the more prestigious Ten Most Wanted List.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.63,0:35:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是巧合 还是你又开始侦办我的案件?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is this coincidence, or are you back on the case?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.94,0:35:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,果真如此 那好 我将从退隐的地方走出\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}If so, goody goody, because I need to come out of retirement{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.48,0:35:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再回到公众的生活中去\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}and return to public life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.20,0:35:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以想像出 你正坐在黯淡的地下室里\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I imagine you sitting in a dark basement room{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.86,0:35:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埋首于纸堆和电脑荧光幕中\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}bent over papers and computer screens.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.99,0:35:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说对了吧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Is that accurate?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.11,0:35:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳探员 请告诉我实话\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Please tell me truly, Special Agent Starling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.50,0:35:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请珍重 你的老友 汉尼拔医生\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Regards, your old pal, Hannibal Lecter, MD.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.04,0:35:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,附注 我看得出这不是你的本意\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}PS: Clearly this new assignment is not your choice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.38,0:35:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是某种交换\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Rather, I suppose, it is part of the bargain.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.47,0:35:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是你仍然接受了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}But you accepted it, Clarice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.34,0:35:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的职责是毁灭我\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yourjob is to craft my doom{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.05,0:35:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以实在不知道 在信尾该怎么祝你\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}so I'm not sure how well I should wish you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.93,0:36:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我相信 我们将会有很多乐趣\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but I'm sure we'll have a lot of fun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.48,0:36:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回见\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Ta-ta.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.27,0:36:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"汉"\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}"H."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.53,0:36:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在信上\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}On the letter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.86,0:36:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到一个局部的指纹\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}there's one partial fingerprint here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.78,0:36:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-可是在法庭上还嫌不够  -这一定是他\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Not enough to hold up in court. -I know it's him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.95,0:36:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想知道他在哪里写这封信\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Where he was when he wrote it is what I need.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.29,0:36:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜从信纸上看不出来\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Well, the paper isn't gonna help.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.70,0:36:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中有亚麻纤维的成份 应该属于奢侈品\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes, it's linen fibre, yes, it's on the expensive side{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.70,0:36:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是却不罕见 全球至少 有上千家店会卖这种信纸\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}but it's not so rare that you won't find it in a thousand stationery stores throughout the world.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.30,0:36:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于墨水和腊也是一样\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's the same with the ink, and the same with the wax.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.09,0:36:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有拉斯维加斯的邮戳\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And your Las Vegas postmark?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.51,0:36:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你打赌 是由重寄邮件服务公司寄的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You can check it out, but I'll bet you it came from a remailing service.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.39,0:36:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来赌城是他最后的停留点\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Las Vegas would be the last place he'd be.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.81,0:36:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的品味不该这么低\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It'd be an assault on his sense of taste.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.44,0:37:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你不觉得 有目光在你身上游动吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Don't you feel eyes moving over your body, Clarice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.44,0:37:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当然会感觉得到\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I hardly see how you couldn't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.08,0:37:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人的眼光 会在喜欢的东西上游走\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}And don't your eyes move over the things you want?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.66,0:37:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我是怎么回事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}All right, then. Tell me how.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.70,0:37:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.08,0:37:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在轮到你告诉我了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's your turn to tell me, Clarice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.34,0:37:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你想再骗我到那个 布满动物传染病的岛上去?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You don't have any more vacations to sell on Anthrax Island.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.75,0:37:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了我们这是公平交易\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Quid pro quo, Clarice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.96,0:37:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你一件事 你也得告诉我一件事\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I tell you things, you tell me things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.88,0:37:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不谈案子 就说你自己吧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Not about this case. About yourself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.35,0:37:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是公平交易\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Quid pro quo.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.06,0:37:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史黛琳 你愿意吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Yes or no, Clarice?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.32,0:37:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,手霜\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Hand cream.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.12,0:37:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中有龙涎香\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Raw ambergris base.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.95,0:37:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,田纳西的熏衣草\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Tennessee lavender.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.33,0:37:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有一些别的东西\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Trace of something else.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.38,0:37:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,羊毛\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Fleece.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.59,0:38:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Lovely.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.54,0:38:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-龙涎香是什么东西?  -它来自鲸鱼\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-What's ambergris? -Ambergris is a whale product.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.50,0:38:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然我们也喜欢但不准进口\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Alas, much as we'd like to, we can't import it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.43,0:38:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这会危害到稀有动物\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Endangered Species Act.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.30,0:38:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-在哪些国家是合法呢?  -毫无疑问的是日本\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Where isn't it illegal? -Japan, of course.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.72,0:38:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另外还有一些欧洲国家\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Couple of places in Europe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我肯定在巴黎 罗马 阿姆斯特丹可以找到\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}You'd almost certainly find it somewhere in Paris,Rome,Amsterdam.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.56,0:38:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伦敦也有可能\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Maybe London.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.90,0:38:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种香味 是照客人的指示以手工合成的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}This bouquet was hand-engineered to someone's specifications.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.40,0:38:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-能知道是出自哪个商店吗?  -可以 我们会给你一张名单\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Is there a way of knowing which shops? -Of course. We'll give you a list.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.24,0:38:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放心 不会太长\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It'll be short.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.54,0:38:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要歌剧票\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I need opera tickets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.88,0:38:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我身上没有了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I don't think I got any on me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.43,0:38:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说是卖光了\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's sold out, whatever it's called.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.05,0:38:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是他那个年轻漂亮的太太 吵着要去看歌剧\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}It's the pretty, young wife with the ever-open beak who needs opera tickets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.56,0:39:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-班尼第  -什么事?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Benetti. -What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.06,0:39:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,倒带\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Rewind it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.40,0:39:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行 我正在拷贝\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}I can't rewind it. I'm making a copy. I'm recording.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.96,0:39:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么带子?\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}What is this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.37,0:39:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是位在斯卡拉大道上 香水店的防盗录影带\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}Security camera from a perfume shop in Via Della Scala.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.25,0:39:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国调查局经由国际刑警组 向我们要求的\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}FBI, through Interpol, requested a copy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.33,0:39:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为什么?  -他们没说\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-Why? -They didn't say.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.72,0:39:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没说?  -他们的态度很奇怪\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}-They didn't say? -No. It was actually kind of weird.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.93,0:39:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摆明了不告诉我们\N{\fntahoma\fs10\1c&H0080FF&}They were making a point not to say.{\r}
